<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5181] Accessibility fixes needed for release notes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5181</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The top-level RELEASE-NOTES.html file uses the &amp;lt;blockquote&amp;gt; tag to indent the text. This looks nice and improves readability, but it violates the WCAG accessibility guideline 3.7, which says, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Mark up quotations. Do not use quotation markup for formatting effects such as indentation.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can use a CSS stylesheet for formatting, however.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
